  "text": "The performance of a small target algorithm is generally evaluated on the basis of three criteria: target enhancement, background suppression, and detection accuracy. The signal-to-clutter gain (SCRG) is widely used for evaluating the performance of target enhancement [CITATION_1] . However, the clutter around targets is purely clean after using our method, which makes the SCRG approach infinity. Thus, we adopted the local contrast gain (LCG) to evaluate the target enhancement ability. The LCG is defined as:",
